				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today. And by the way, I&#8217;ll be on vacation next week. See you in December!</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Conference Board Leading Economic Index <a href="//www.conference-board.org/pdf_free/press/PressPDF_5328_1416477607.pdf">rose sharply</a> in October indicating that economic growth will continue through early 2015.</li>
<li>Hereâs <a href="//www.inc.com/gene-marks/the-leading-indicator-that-few-talk-about.html">another leading indicator</a> that few people are talking about: the success of midsize companies.</li>
<li>The global economy&#8217;s slowdown is <a href="//seekingalpha.com/article/2699585-the-global-economys-slowdown-weighs-on-u-s-manufacturing">weighing on</a> manufacturing, but Philadelphia-area factories grew <a href="//www.mbtmag.com/news/2014/11/philly-area-factories-growing-most-21-years">by the most</a> in 21 years.</li>
<li>The price consumers paid for sugar <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/economics/2014/11/20/sugar-prices-got-sweeter-for-consumers-in-october/?m">fell the most</a> on record last month.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Retail</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The owner of a New York cookbook store talks about <a href="//www.grubstreet.com/2014/11/bonnie-slotnick-cookbooks-interview.html">why she may be forced</a> to move.</li>
<li>Apple Pay <a href="//techcrunch.com/2014/11/20/apple-is-coming-to-the-aid-of-small-retailers/">could revolutionize</a> small-business payment apps.</li>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"> <span id="more-90414"></span>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3038663/how-we-push-small-businesses-out-of-the-legal-marijuana-market?partner=rss">Big Cannabis</a> is already squeezing out the marijuana entrepreneurs.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Start-Up</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A lot of notable investors &#8212; and a former head of the Small Business Administration &#8212; are <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/practically-every-notable-founder-in-silicon-valley-just-invested-in-this-startup-2014-11">investing in a payroll start-up</a>.</li>
<li>That defiant television-streaming start-up has finally <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/240070?hootPostID=ca757ff44a508998bfaac8c4abdda577">filed for bankruptcy</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Immigration</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The president&#8217;s immigration plan will <a href="//www.vox.com/2014/11/21/7256341/immigration-economic-impact">help the economy</a> &#8212; but not as much as Congressional action would.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s how the plan <a href="//www.marketplace.org/topics/economy/troubled-detroit-could-immigration-help#.VG9fBk9xnDg.twitter">could help cities like Detroit</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here is why we <a href="//www.vox.com/2014/11/20/7254877/keynes-work-leisure">still haven&#8217;t reduced</a> the number of hours we work in a week.</li>
<li>Half of employees say they <a href="https://hbr.org/2014/11/half-of-employees-dont-feel-respected-by-their-bosses">donât feel respected</a> by their bosses.</li>
<li><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/11/21/business/falling-wages-at-factories-squeeze-the-middle-class.html">Falling wages at factories</a> are squeezing the middle class.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Swipely&#8217;s transaction-processing <a href="//bostinno.streetwise.co/2014/11/20/swipely-small-business-marketing-software-hits-restaurants-sweet-spot/">volume is up</a> 100 percent in six months.</li>
<li>Here are some <a href="//fitsmallbusiness.com/dental-marketing-ideas/">marketing ideas</a> just for dentists.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s what you can learn from dead companies that <a href="//www.cio.com/article/2850122/innovation/disruptive-technology-dead-companies-do-tell-tales.html?utm_campaign=sflow_tweet#tk.rss_all">did not hear the footsteps coming</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Business Travel<br />
</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A seasoned traveler says you <a href="//timmaurer.com/2014/11/20/business-travelers-skip-in-flight-wi-fi-to-increase-productivity-and-save-money/">can be more productive</a> on a plane <em>without</em> Wi-Fi.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Customer Service</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Comcast wants to <a href="//www.theverge.com/2014/11/20/7255781/comcast-tests-letting-customers-track-their-cable-technicians-eta">let its customers track</a> when their cable technician will arrive.</li>
<li>A tree takes down electrical wires near his house, and a homeowner <a href="//www.thestar.com/opinion/commentary/2014/11/19/my_year_in_customer_service_hell.html">spends a year</a> in &#8220;customer service hell.&#8221;</li>
<li>Graco is recalling almost <a href="//time.com/3598239/graco-strollers-5-million/">5 million strollers</a> after complaints that childrenâs fingers were at risk.</li>
<li>A used car dealership is <a href="//www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/11/20/drivetime-fine-cfpb_n_6193002.html">hit with an $8 million</a> fine for harassing customers.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Health Care</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Obama administration said it <a href="//www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-11-20/obamacare-s-subscriber-rolls-include-unpublicized-dental-plans.html">erroneously calculated</a> the number of people with health coverage under the Affordable Care Act.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Online</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Netflix <a href="//qz.com/299989/netflix-now-accounts-for-35-of-bandwidth-usage-in-the-us-and-canada/">now accounts for</a> 35 percent of Internet bandwidth in the United States and Canada.</li>
<li>Amazon <a href="https://gigaom.com/2014/11/20/amazon-quietly-commits-to-100-clean-energy-for-aws-but-gives-no-details/">quietly commits</a> to 100-percent clean energy for its cloud services.</li>
<li>Britain <a href="//www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/nov/20/webcam-hackers-watching-you-watchdog-warns?CM">moves to shut down</a> Russian hackers who are streaming live British webcam footage.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A Massachusetts town <a href="//www.scientificamerican.com/article/massachusetts-town-stubs-out-plan-to-ban-tobacco-sales/">blocks a plan</a> to ban tobacco sales.</li>
<li>A bike shop in New York is <a href="//www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20141120/west-village/citi-bike-drove-me-out-of-business-west-village-bike-shop-owner-says">closing for good</a> in December, and the owner blames Citi Bike.</li>
<li>Montana <a href="//www.abcfoxmontana.com/story/27427883/montana-sees-rise-in-small-business-distilleries#.V">sees a rise</a> in small-business distilleries.</li>
<li>Shreveport, La., celebrates its fourth &#8220;<a href="//www.ksla.com/story/27432707/pop-up-businesses-popping-in-downtown-shreveport">pop up</a>&#8221; business event.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A cab service in London <a href="//mashable.com/2014/11/20/gettaxi-deal/?">is offering</a> Â£5 rides.</li>
<li>This is how <a href="//thebillfold.com/2014/11/how-to-get-eu-citizenship-country-by-country/">to get</a> European Union citizenship, country by country.</li>
<li>Some of India&#8217;s biggest brick-and-mortar retail chains <a href="//www.cnet.com/news/google-emerging-markets-phone-gets-hung-up-in-india-as-retailers-cry-foul/#ftag=CAD590a51e">are refusing</a> to sell Android One devices.</li>
<li>A drone with <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/102204338">a sprig of mistletoe</a> and a fitted âKiss Camâ is flying around a T.G.I. Friday&#8217;s restaurant in Britain.</li>
<li>Canadian hockey <a href="//cheezburger.com/66393601?u">fans finish</a> the âStar Spangled Bannerâ after a microphone fails.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>SAP <a href="//money.cnn.com/news/newsfeeds/articles/prnewswire/SF72137.htm">holds a summit</a> for small- and medium-sized companies.</li>
<li>The world&#8217;s <a href="//www.gizmodo.com.au/2014/11/the-worlds-most-futuristic-cruise-ship-made-me-miss-the-past/">most futuristic</a> cruise ship makes this technology writer miss the past.</li>
<li>A virtual seat <a href="//mashable.com/2014/11/20/paul-mccartney-vr-app/?u">beside Paul McCartney&#8217;s piano</a> during a concert could cost you as little as $10.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the <a href="//www.marksgroup.net">Marks Group</a>, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
